TITLE: Accessing Theme Properties with useTheme Hook - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates how to access theme properties, such as colors, within a component using the `useTheme()` hook provided by React Native Paper.  The theme object contains customizable styles that can be applied to various UI elements. Requires import of `useTheme` from 'react-native-paper'.
SOURCE: https://github.com/callstack/react-native-paper/blob/main/docs/docs/guides/02-theming.mdx#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
import * as React from 'react';
import { useTheme } from 'react-native-paper';

export default function PaymentScreen() {
  const theme = useTheme();

  return <View style={{ backgroundColor: theme.colors.primary }} />;
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Applying Theme with PaperProvider - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to wrap the root component with `PaperProvider` to enable theming support in React Native Paper. This is the foundational step for applying custom themes to the entire application.
SOURCE: https://github.com/callstack/react-native-paper/blob/main/docs/docs/guides/02-theming.mdx#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
import * as React from 'react';
import { PaperProvider } from 'react-native-paper';
import App from './src/App';

export default function Main() {
  return (
    <PaperProvider>
      <App />
    </PaperProvider>
  );
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Extending Default Theme - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to extend the default React Native Paper theme with custom properties and colors. This allows developers to customize the look and feel of components while maintaining the base styling. Requires import of `MD3LightTheme` or `MD2LightTheme` as `DefaultTheme` from 'react-native-paper'.
SOURCE: https://github.com/callstack/react-native-paper/blob/main/docs/docs/guides/02-theming.mdx#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
import * as React from 'react';
import {
  MD3LightTheme as DefaultTheme,
  PaperProvider,
} from 'react-native-paper';
import App from './src/App';

const theme = {
  ...DefaultTheme,
  // Specify custom property
  myOwnProperty: true,
  // Specify custom property in nested object
  colors: {
    ...DefaultTheme.colors,
    myOwnColor: '#BADA55',
  },
};

export default function Main() {
  return (
    <PaperProvider theme={theme}>
      <App />
    </PaperProvider>
  );
}
```

