TITLE: Using the useAppTheme Hook - TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript code demonstrates how to use the custom `useAppTheme` hook in a component to access custom theme properties. It retrieves a custom color from the theme and applies it to a View.
SOURCE: https://github.com/callstack/react-native-paper/blob/main/docs/docs/guides/02-theming.mdx#_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
import * as React from 'react';
import { useAppTheme } from './App';

export default function HomeScreen() {
  const {
    colors: { brandPrimary },
  } = useAppTheme();

  return <View style={{ backgroundColor: brandPrimary }}>...</View>;
}
```

