TITLE: Dynamic AppBar Title with getHeaderTitle (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet dynamically sets the AppBar title using `getHeaderTitle` from `@react-navigation/elements`. It retrieves the title based on the current route and options passed to the `CustomNavigationBar` component. Requires `@react-navigation/elements` and `react-native-paper`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/callstack/react-native-paper/blob/main/docs/docs/guides/09-react-navigation.md#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { Appbar } from 'react-native-paper';
import { getHeaderTitle } from '@react-navigation/elements';

export default function CustomNavigationBar({ route, options }) {
  const title = getHeaderTitle(options, route.name);

  return (
    <Appbar.Header>
      <Appbar.Content title={title} />
    </Appbar.Header>
  );
}
```

