TITLE: Applying Theme to a Component - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript code shows how to apply a theme directly to a React Native Paper component by passing the `theme` prop.  The component's theme is merged with the global `PaperProvider` theme.
SOURCE: https://github.com/callstack/react-native-paper/blob/main/docs/docs/guides/02-theming.mdx#_snippet_14

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
import * as React from 'react';
import { Button } from 'react-native-paper';

export default function ButtonExample() {
  return (
    <Button raised theme={{ roundness: 3 }}>
      Press me
    </Button>
  );
}
```

