TITLE: Theming: Colors Configuration
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates the new color palette structure for theming in Material You (MD3). It showcases the properties required within the `colors` object, including primary, secondary, tertiary, surface, background, and error colors, along with their corresponding 'on' colors and elevation levels.
SOURCE: https://github.com/callstack/react-native-paper/blob/main/docs/docs/guides/10-migration-guide-to-5.0.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
theme: {
  /* ... */
  colors: {
    primary,
    primaryContainer,
    secondary,
    secondaryContainer,
    tertiary,
    tertiaryContainer,
    surface,
    surfaceVariant,
    surfaceDisabled,
    background,
    error,
    errorContainer,
    onPrimary,
    onPrimaryContainer,
    onSecondary,
    onSecondaryContainer,
    onTertiary,
    onTertiaryContainer,
    onSurface,
    onSurfaceVariant,
    onSurfaceDisabled,
    onError,
    onErrorContainer,
    onBackground,
    outline,
    shadow,
