TITLE: HTML Template
DESCRIPTION: This `index.html` file serves as the HTML template for the web application. It includes meta tags for character set, compatibility, and viewport settings. It also defines basic styling and includes a div with id `root` where the React application will be rendered and a script tag to load the bundled JavaScript.
SOURCE: https://github.com/callstack/react-native-paper/blob/main/docs/docs/guides/05-react-native-web.md#_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: HTML
CODE:
```
<!doctype html>
<head>
  <meta charSet="utf-8" />
  <meta httpEquiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge" />

  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,minimum-scale=1,initial-scale=1" />

  <title>App</title>

  <style>
    html, body, #root {
      height: 100%;
    }

    #root {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div id="root"></div>
  <script src="app.bundle.js"></script>
</body>
```

